<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Football News</title>
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
</head>
<body class="bg-light">

<%- include('partials/navbar') %>

<!-- MAIN CONTENT -->
<div class="container my-4">

    <!-- Headline -->
    <div class="card shadow mb-4">
        <div class="card-body">
            <span class="badge bg-danger mb-2">Premier League</span>
            <h2 class="card-title mt-2">
                Man City player ratings vs Crystal Palace:
                Haaland & Foden down plucky Eagles
            </h2>
            <p class="text-muted">
                Manchester City 3–0 Crystal Palace • Selhurst Park
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Article Content -->
    <div class="card shadow mb-4">
        <div class="card-body">
            <p>
                Erling Haaland and Phil Foden raised their game as Manchester City beat
                Crystal Palace 3-0 despite producing an underwhelming performance in
                south London. Palace hit the woodwork in both halves, but City were
                clinical when it mattered.
            </p>

            <p>
                Haaland gave Pep Guardiola’s side the lead in the 40th minute with a
                towering header following a move involving more than 20 passes.
                Phil Foden doubled the advantage in the second half before Haaland
                sealed the win with a late penalty.
            </p>

            <p>
                Crystal Palace showed plenty of intent, striking the post twice and
                troubling City on the counter, but the visitors managed the game
                well to maintain pressure on Arsenal at the top of the table.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Player Ratings -->
    <div class="card shadow mb-4">
        <div class="card-header bg-dark text-white">
            <h5 class="mb-0">Player Ratings (Man City)</h5>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
                <li class="list-group-item">
                    <strong>Erling Haaland</strong> – 7/10  
                    <span class="text-muted d-block">
                        Clinical finishing, two goals, decisive presence.
                    </span>
                </li>
                <li class="list-group-item">
                    <strong>Phil Foden</strong> – 7/10  
                    <span class="text-muted d-block">
                        Brilliant second-half strike, constant threat.
                    </span>
                </li>
                <li class="list-group-item">
                    <strong>Rayan Cherki</strong> – 7/10  
                    <span class="text-muted d-block">
                        Excellent footwork and key assist.
                    </span>
                </li>
                <li class="list-group-item">
                    <strong>Matheus Nunes</strong> – 7/10  
                    <span class="text-muted d-block">
                        Perfect cross for Haaland’s opener.
                    </span>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Most Read -->
    <div class="card shadow">
        <div class="card-header bg-secondary text-white">
            <h5 class="mb-0">Most Read</h5>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <ol>
                <li>Fortunate Arsenal need two own goals to beat Wolves</li>
                <li>Raphinha fires Barca seven points clear</li>
                <li>Mainoo situation sparks debate at United</li>
                <li>Messi visibly uncomfortable as GOAT Tour turns ugly</li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    </div>

</div>

<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
